"According to the Yogis, there are two nerve currents in the spinal column, called Pingal&acirc; and Id&acirc;, and a hollow canal called Sushumn&acirc; running through the spinal cord. At the lower end of the hollow canal is what the Yogis call the "Lotus of the Kundalini". They describe it as triangular in form in which, in the symbolical language of the Yogis, there is a power called the Kundalini, coiled up. When that Kundalini awakes, it tries to force a passage through this hollow canal, and as it rises step by step, as it were, layer after layer of the mind becomes open and all the different visions and wonderful powers come to the Yogi. When it reaches the brain, the Yogi is perfectly detached from the body and mind; the soul finds itself free."<br><br>
- Swami Vivekananda, "The Psychic Prana" (Advanced raja yoga class, Jan 4, 1896, New York), Raja Yoga, Complete Works: Vol 1
</p>
